        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-18T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-18T11:00:00-05:00" n="162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/2–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-18T23:00:00+07:00">February 18, 1945—11 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m.</hi>]</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 18—10:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>243. [Text of National Government’s draft of January 24.<note n="1" xml:id="d162fn1">For presentation of this draft by Wang Shih-chieh to the
                        Ambassador in China, see the Ambassador’s telegram No. 242, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>] Besides the three points contained in
                    the previous Government proposal,<note n="2" xml:id="d162fn2">Telegram No. 143,
                        January 31, 8 p.m., from the Ambassador in China, not printed.</note> the
                    National Government is prepared to take the three following measures:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text of Statement by Chinese Government Representatives printed on
                        <ref target="#pg_185">page 185</ref>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
